
<h4 style="color:#72A0C1; font-family:verdana; font-size: 15px; font-weight: 200;">Connections Checks</h4>
<p style="font-family:Arial; font-size: 13px;">
The max_used_connections should ideally be lower than the max_connections value, as having it greater than the set value for max_connections could result in the mariadb server hitting the: “Too Many Connections” error.
</p>
<p style="font-family:Arial; font-size: 13px;">
Innodb_stats_on_metadata should ideally be set to OFF. If set to ON, Innodb index statistics are unnecessarily updated when running some queries like SHOW TABLE STATUS, etc, and querying Information_Schema table like TABLES, STATISTICS, etc. This causes unnecessary IO loads to the system.
</p>

